news.title: China plans $4.2 billion fund to buy realty from developers
news.para: The fund will "invest in existing assets" of real estate companies and renovate the properties into rental housing, the lender said in a statement to the Shanghai stock exchange on Friday.

news.title: Delhi: 1,000 homes demolished, over 5,800 people hit, says HLRN report
news.para: A  new report by Housing and Land Rights Network (HLRN) says that the government authorities, at both the central and state levels, demolished over 36,480 homes in 2021, thereby evicting over 2 lakh people from their homes across the country.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to auction 30 industrial plots on freehold basis
news.para: In February this year, UT administrator Banwarilal Purohit had approved auctioning of all UT vacant/unsold industrial and commercial properties on a freehold basis.

news.title: Builder encroached on Khar West plot, Bombay HC told in report
news.para: The August 29 report was called for by Chief Justice Dipankar Datta and Justice Makarand Karnik while hearing a PIL by three residents that the Slum Rehabilitation Authority had let Integrated Realty Projects to construct on it.

news.title: Delhi RERA directs Brilliant Etoile to stop booking, not to seek money
news.para: The project was registered with RERA in July 2018 and the original schedule for completion was August, 2021. The regulator had in June 2020 granted an extension of nine months for completion of the project due to the first wave of Covid-19 pandemic, till May this year.

news.title: Forum orders Kanpur development body to pay 7% interest to complainant
news.para: Complainant Kanti Singh, a resident of Barra- 2, on February 27, 2016 had applied in KDA for a plot and deposited Rs 4,23,000 as ten percent of the cost of plot after allotment.

news.title: EY India renews lease for 40,330 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Dadar
news.para: The firm will be paying a total nearly Rs 20 crore as rentals for this office during the entire tenure of the lease based on monthly rentals of Rs 165 per sq ft.

news.title: Jaipur: NGT orders probe into issuance of patta under Nahargarh SEZ
news.para: NGT has directed that the inquiry should find out person/persons responsible for the issue of any kind of patta or transfer of forest land without the requisite approval of the competent authority under the relevant rules.

news.title: Mumbai: Land ownership transfer & redevelopment issues haunt societies as they rush to complete audits
news.para: According to them due to covid several societies took time till March this year to clear their audit for earlier fiscal 2020-21 and thus have backlog for recently ended fiscal to be cleared.

news.title: Karnataka government allotted multiple homes to same families: CAG
news.para: An adult earning member (irrespective of marital status) could be treated as a separate household if he/she does not own a pucca house in his or her name in any part of India.

news.title: MEDCL restores power supply for essential services in Lavasa
news.para: The MSEDCL had on September 17 disconnected 131 connections in the hill city project for non-payment of dues of running up to Rs 22.78 crore pending since August 2018. "Seven of the connections were restored," the MSEDCL official said.

news.title: Britain cuts stamp duty tax on property purchases
news.para: The nil-band threshold for first-time buyers will also increase to 425,000 from 300,000 pounds, he told lawmakers on Friday, adding that the changes are permanent and effective immediately.

news.title: Housing society files PIL against Pune civic body for approach road delay
news.para: The residents of Kumar Primavera Society, having 550 flats, filed the PIL supported by adjacent societies in the area. They said that non-completion of the road has also inconvenienced other housing societies in the area.

news.title: Ludhiana: Engineers' body approaches CMO against illegal colonies under Glada
news.para: Members of Council of Engineers (COE) alleged that despite officials claiming otherwise, there has been little check on illegal colonies.

news.title: Indore: Illegally developed 20 acres may now be home for poor
news.para: Instructions have been issued to IMC, T&CP and the revenue department to put a ban on giving any permission along with registration of property (sale/purchase) of the land. Market value of said around 20 acres of land is stated to be around Rs 500 Crore.
